In this speech at a private residence in Golden Beach, Florida, President Biden expresses his support for Congressman Charlie Crist and emphasizes the importance of the upcoming elections. He reflects on his decision to run for president and discusses the need to restore decency and unity in America. Biden criticizes the Republican Party for its response to the violence in Charlottesville and its failure to condemn the Capitol insurrection. He also highlights the importance of preserving women's rights, particularly in relation to reproductive freedom. Biden mentions the progress made in passing legislation and funding for infrastructure, the environment, and law enforcement. He criticizes the opposition's stance on taxes and corporate accountability. The president emphasizes the significance of state elections and their impact on voting rights and the future of the country. He concludes by urging the audience to consider the long-term consequences of their votes.